        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=14262&TOPIC_ID=2015&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Inter%2DCaster+Balance&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> If they would ask me, I would balance it this way:</P><P>1. Enchanters stick out, they are no damage dealer, they are for crowd control/slow/haste/crack, they are wanted in groups and they are balanced. PERIOD</P><P>2. Damage dealers are Wiz, Mage, Necro. </P><P>a) Wizard<BR>This must be the master of damage dealt in a SHORT period of time. Noone should rival a wizard when it comes to fights up to 30 secs or to ONE fight.</P><P>They have their problems with damage sustained over time though. If you look at the wizard over the time of one hour... he should be the last one of the 3. </P><P>I always understood the wizard as an emergency damage dealer... something goes wrong, here comes the wizard and nukes 3 enemies down with the blink of an eye. </P><P>b) Mages <BR>2nd best in short time encounters... they can deal a good punch over time because of their pets (should rank 2nd). Maybe their pets should have good ac/resistance/hp so that their pet can tank even the very hard mobs for a while. So this could help with a pull that went wrong.</P><P>c) Necros<BR>Master of long fights, master of damage dealt over time. Noone (and I include melees here) should rival the necro in fights or exp group situations that go over a long time. Would be good if the necro has a better mez to help with adds. Some kind of lure mez, that lasts 18 secs.<BR>Necros should rank 3rd in short time fights.</P><P><BR>OVERALL Balance:<BR>the 3 tank classes (war,shd,Pal) should rank last with damage output. They can take quite a punch though. Without them no situation can be successful because they are capable of SOAKING damage.</P><P>Shamans, Enchs, Clerics are fine, they make some encounters possible, without them some things are simply not possible.</P><P>The 3 damage dealing melees (ranger, monk, rogue) should rank well above the tank classes, but behind the casting classes in short time encounters AND in long time encounters. Why is that so? Because they are very safe in groups (evade, FD) when it comes to aggro management. Monk is important in groups because of FD pulling. </P><P>Casters should have a hard time dealing with aggro management. So casters CAN dish out uber damage, but will they survive it? I would raise the low health frenzy of mobs ( you know when the mobs will stick to you like glue) to 2 bubbles of health. So if the MT has lower hp than 2 bubs, the wizard can nuke it down in safety. Maybe it could be a risky tactic to let the MT stay below 2 bubs of hp so that casters can make short work of the mobs.</P><P>Beastmasters should rank together with rogues when it comes to long time damage dealing. </P><P>Druids are very difficult to balance IMHO. Maybe they should get a better heal so that they can rival the cleric a bit. They have good nukes and can do some kind of ghetto mez though. <BR>Bards are a welcome addition to each group and are balanced imho. Their mana songs make them welcome in raid situations. <BR>Druids and bards should not have their strenght in damage dealing though. </P><P>Something forgotten? Dunno, I bet I have, but I end for now.</P><P>With my Vision any class would have its niche in the exp situation and in the raid situation. What makes it so difficult for Verant? EQ was balanced pre Kunark (except rogues, rangers), after this they slowly changed it all to the melees. That was wrong, Verant sees that and will help the casters in the near future. Trust Verant, they did a great job when they balanced Pallies, Rangers and Rogues.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
