			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=638')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=14267&TOPIC_ID=2015&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Inter%2DCaster+Balance&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> This is a very good post. Thoughtful and articulate. Well done Raz. I would like to congratulate you on an excellent rebutal of FOH's Kruegen found on the Magician's Tower. The link to your post can be found here and is very good reading:</P><P><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessage?topicID=4540.topic" target="_blank">http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessage?topicID=4540.topic</a></P><P>Let me just start off by saying I think I think Verant is misguided in their attempts to "balance" casters vs. melee because of the fact that healer classes have been lumped in with pure casters. Look at the nerf of the mage summoned items with regard to Complete Heal and you'll see how this problem has surfaced.</P><P>It is my opinion that Clerics are perhaps the 2nd most popular class in EverQuest at lvl 60 and Shamans who are well above the average lvl 60 population are currently well balanced and in no need of assistance by Verant. I have found an interesting website with data on lvl 60 players which supports this:</P><P><a href="http://www.geocities.com/eqcensus/" target="_blank">http://www.geocities.com/eqcensus/</a></P><P>The category "casters" is just too broad in terms of the need for balancing. At the very least it's "pure casters" that truly need the help and if we break it down even further it's the pet classes within that subset that are in true danger of becoming useless at level 60. Mages and Necromancers are most commonly found at the bottom of the list of lvl 60 players and usually constitute from 3%-4% of the total population. </P><P>I enjoyed your analysis of the various forms of utility that each class enjoys. However I do believe that the totality of a casters usefullness in groups and on raids would probably be rank like this:</P><P>Enchanter, Wizard, Mage and Necro</P><P>I've never heard of a raid cancelled by a lack of mages and necros. Yet, I've heard of raids cancelled because no clerics, enchanters or wizards showed up. The truth is mages and necros are non-essential classes. We are just window dressing in the grand scheme of things. The designers at Verant just never got around to giving us some role to play in the end game. Head on over to LOS's or FOH's website and check the roster of lvl 60 players. You will soon notice that the lowest numbers of classes represented are mages and necros. Legacy of Steel has I think 18 lvl 60 clerics and 2 necros and 2 mages if I'm not mistaken. That speaks volumes. Uber guilds recruit the classes that are needed for the high level end game in EQ.</P><P>Pet classes consistently at the bottom of most guild's list of classes to be recruited because even guild leaders realize that they are non-essential. What I find upsetting is the negative attitude by certain Verant personnel directed against pet classes. Abashi remarked in Dec. 2000 that "necros should have to pay...". Seems necros deserve to be forever gimped at lvl 60 because of a few easy levels in Oasis. Then Abashi admitted at a recent Fan Faire that he wished COH had never been made which naturally caused outrage in the mage community. </P><P>With Brad's departure, we can only hope as pet classes that our dwindling ranks and legitimate concerns will finally be addressed by Verant. Wizards have received some major upgrades with Luclin and are now desired in AE groups and for damage on raids. How about the pet classes now?</P><P>I think the pet classes need some serious upgrades and fixes in order for us to remain viable. The news from test about 1 sec casting time for pets is welcome. Other issues like pets that don't agro mobs as compensation for bad pathing (NPC pets are non-agro), pets stealing experience, pet damage and stats also need to be seriously looked at. </P><P>We are now on the verge of having yet another expansion being released in Norrath: Planes of Power. If nothing is changed we will have pets that are 4 expansions old. I defy any warrior, rogue, or monk to use weapons and gear from 4 expansions ago against the mobs of today. Clearly our pets need to be upgraded to face the challenge of today's ultra, uber, flurrying, MR mobs.</P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer (un-retired)<BR>The Nameless<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
