        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Your comment regarding wizzies getting adjusted first:</P><P>- I think this is more due to the fact that this is the simplest and easiest int class to tweek, therefore, VI will most likely provide the most/earliest enhancements to the wizzie class.</P><P>To improve/balance the necro:</P><P>- In theory, its easy.  Let us be masters of damage over time by allowing necro's the to be the damage kings in 5+ minute encounters on mobs with 100k to 1million hitpoints.  Do this by providing us upgrades to splurt, have chilling embrace scale like funeral pyre does and allow multiple necro dots to stack, without a 15 buff restriction on a mob.  In addition, allow necro dots to crit by amplifying the damage over the same duration, scaling similarly to how DD's crit for wizzies and other nuking classes.</P><P>Unfortuneately, VI has been and will be reluctant to give necro's any enhancements in damage capacity.  They probably fear by doing so, they'll only enhance the necro's ability to solo, which as we all know, is very anti VI 'vision' and is from Vi's point of view, detrimental to the class interdependancy theme they've always advocated.  In addition, there are techical obstacles to overcome with allowing multiple dots to stack.  This is a serious issue as a raid/guild experiences diminishing returns on the additional necro's attending a raid or event.</P><P>I'm concerned about alot of things.  For example, wizzie nukes, especially when factoring in crit's, are rivaling the mana efficiency of our dots, which should never be the case.  Also, I see vi answering the necro balance issues with more utility spells, which only further takes us away from what i feel our game role should be - the masters of damage over time.  I'm confident that this caster balance will bring improvements to all classes, but i'm very cautious with my optimism, anticipating minor adjustments to the necromancer class, with major ones for wizzies.</P><P>The answers are simple, but the solutions are not.  Do my suggestions overpower the necro class? I hardly think so.  Unfortuneately i dont think VI has the same opinion.</P><P><a  href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675">Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
