        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I find it rather amusing that VI dislikes soloing so much.  Sure, EQ is a social game, but thanks to chat channels, I don't even need a guild to have a little background chatter when I'm soloing.  I'd honestly like to see why it is so against the vision to solo.  Does it violate risk vs reward?  I don't think so, quite honestly it is much harder to solo than it is to be in a group, not to mention a whole hell of a lot safer in a group.  Then there are the added benefits of almost always being able to get a res while in a group... etc.<BR>Even if for some screwy reason they do think it violates risk vs reward, VI needs to take a hard look at AE groups.  AE groups are quite funny in the fact that there is very little risk whatsoever and the experience really rolls in.  I used to watch a group go through the south wing in Howling stones, then through the basement and back up to the entrance in 20 minutes.  Every mob in their way was slain.<BR>I'm not calling for a nerf of AE groups, I'm just asking for a little consistency in their policy *snicker*.  If AE groups aren't this terrible thing to the vision, then neither should soloing.  They <i>should</i> give us needed upgrades even if it makes us solo better.</P><P>EDIT: Grammar<BR>[59 Defiler] Jered Caladine (Dark Elf): E'ci<BR>Wielder of the talking duck!<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22847" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22847</a></P><P>Edited by - jered on 03/26/2002  05:40:24<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
