        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=14325&TOPIC_ID=2015&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Inter%2DCaster+Balance&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Just a few of my thoughts...</P><P>Everything is situational.  Without explaining the specifics of a situation, then you cannot analyze.  It may be better to pick a few specific situations and explain the usefulness of classes in those situations.  </P><P>Regarding magic resistant enemies.  Wizards have their Lure Line of spells that get through practically everything.  I would consider them first in damage to highly resistant mobs.</P><P>Regarding CC.  Wizards are as good as necros in most situations.  I use root and snare for CC most of the time.  Wizards can as well.</P><P>My personal view is that wizards are currently the number one damage dealer in short fights.  If a sorcerer has a full spell book...they can burn their mana down and do more than anyone else currently.  With manaburn...no class comes even close to that DPS.  Wizards are ALREADY kings of the short fights.  With their AA skills in SCF they do even more.  What more do Wizards want?  Do they want to do that damage 7 by 24?  Have you seen an epic wizard eating modrods that chew thru his free epic shield with bard song going and full mana regen items and full mana regen AA abilities.  They have a ton of mana at their disposal if they make the right friends to sustain them for long fights.  They already have this.  What more do they want?  They can critical with their DD more than any other caster when they spend the AA points.  There are no stacking issues.  They have concussion to lower aggro and AA abilities to lower aggro even more.  If I stand back and look at sorcerers at this point, I think...damn...they are overpowered.  The other int casters need something to catch up.</P><P>Necros need DoT stacking and we need our DD's to critical, including Lifeburn.  Other enhancements would be nice.  This is just the baseline.  Remove the peridot cost of our spectre pet.  We have the highest cost gimped pet in the game.  If we keep a gimp pet, take the peridot off.</P><P>Magicians need the most help...IMHO.  But I think people's perceptions are a huge aspect of this.  But here is my idea.  Have a arch-mage summon a pet that lasts one minute.  Have the cast time low, mana low, have the pet not cast stupid spells, just have it proc a lure-based damage effect in addition to physical damage.  Have it come out pre-buffed.  Do not let any buffs land on it.  Give it a ton of HP so it only dies in extreme damage situations and it only lasts one minute.  That is not overpowering.  That should be easy to do.  FTLOG make the mana cost low enough so the mages still have mana to cast modrod2. </P><P>These are just some thoughts.  Certainly not comprehensive.  Just my HO.</P><P>Ishtarra Gemeinseele<BR>Warlock of the Dirty Soul<BR>Uber N00b Extraordinaire<BR>Tunare Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
