        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>When will verant realize that necros need something BIG to bring to the table.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote>This seems like a key question to me.  With the introduction of <i>Rods of Transvergence</i>, twitchers practically need not apply, and this is an unsatisfying role for many in any case.  I like it, because it adds flexibility to our guild and allows our odd mix of classes to achieve their goals, but in many situations it is redundant.  And I am sure you did not sign a pact against your immortal soul with dark powers so that you could give clerics mana.</P><P>Based on the previous posts and the question at the top here, let me throw out a radical and possibly stupid idea.</P><P>How about a really big, really long <i>Damage Over Time</i> spell?  Like 10 or even 15 minutes, for those really big endgame encounters.  Yes, I realize that currently <i>DoTs</i> do not stack, so this would not be completely satisfying, and yes, I realize that in part, that is what a pet is supposed to be.</P><P>But such a long <i>DoT</i> might bring real value to a raid.  It might, for example, neatly counter mob regeneration.  It could also have a mana drain component to make it more useful.</P><P>Brainstorming some other ideas that are consistant with <i>Necromancy</i>.<ul><li>Turning other group members into skeletons that drain their own hitpoints for mana.</li><li>A buff that makes the target immune to fear</li><li>A fear-type stun that is short but difficult to resist <i>(Soandso is paralyzed with fear)</i></li><li>The ability to temporarily resurrect players as skeletons, as a variation of battle rezzing and zerging.  The player skeleton would not suffer from resurrection effects and so could immediately re-enter battle, but might have other limitations <i>(could not loot corpse for instance)</i>or even special powers.</li></ul></P><P>Now THAT would be sight to behold: a <i>Necromancer</i> raising an army of the dead from the corpses of his fallen comrades.</P><P><i>Reckim</i> is dead on:<BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>necros need something BIG to bring to the table.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote>I apologize if these ideas are lame or stupid, but that is what brainstorming is about.  Maybe some lame idea here will give rise to a much better idea by someone else.</P><P>Respectfully,</P><P></P><P>Razamatazz Pizzazz<BR>Mage of a Thousand Words<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
