        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> > Beastlords=Hmmmmm</P><P>Actually I think beastlords are a heavily underestimated class.</P><P>First off they're a low agro melee class, especially with a pet up. A decent warrior NEVER has to worry about a beastlord taunting a mob off him. This is a serious benefit because it saves the warrior on frustration and the cleric on mana.</P><P>However, a beastlord (with pet up) does nearly equal damage to a warrior. I mean yes they're a hybrid class but they can still hold their own. It's nice to have at least one class in the game that can dish out as much damage as it's capable of but not have to worry too much about agroing anything.</P><P>Me playing a warrior, being around rogues and monks piss me off because they're so notoriously incapable of managing agro.</P><P>Beastlords can also slow. On boss fights, this means a beastlord can cast his lower level slow on a mob, tank it for a short bit until the shaman can get a full slow on the mob and the main tank can pick up agro. Sounds like a winner to me.</P><P>They also get some pretty cool buffs.. that one purity spell is nothing to complain about.</P><P><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
