        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I hate it when people respond to a post without reading it. You've got a very good post going and needless flaming ensues, whats this board coming too :)</P><P>Right now the best necro dot is Funeral Pyre. It does 2160 in 54seconds for 450mana, or we can talk efficency which would be more like Splurt which should be 1600 in 96seconds for 237mana. </P><P>Wizards can do 2100 for 540mana. This can crit for 4200 and be enhanced with the focus items to cast faster and do 4640 at least. Faster casting times mean more damage to a wiz but not to a necro who has to wait for his spell to wear off anyway.</P><P>The way to improve DoT spells is to make the stack, not be affected by the 15 buff limit and add a few more high end ones to the 58-60 levels so that necros dont need 9 different spells just to do about half the damamge of a well equiped melee.</P><P>On a long fight I've seen a necro come up to 66% of the rogues damage. This was a necro without Funeral Pyre that did everything he could to be as mana efficient as possible and still be OOM as much as possible :)</P><P>How about these.</P><P>Ancient: River of Blood (upgrade to Vexing Mordainia)</P><P>Version 1:<BR>Damage: 1500<BR>Time: 54 seconds<BR>Mana: 545</P><P>Version 2<BR>Damage: 2000<BR>Time: 54 seconds<BR>Mana: 595</P><P>Version 2 might be more than is needed even at high end. You have to remember though with raid buffs you'll get around 4k hps.</P><P>Ancient: Feast of Blood (splurt upgrade)<BR>Damage 3000<BR>Time: 96 seconds<BR>Mana: 440</P><P>For those that dont know how splurt works, it does very little damage in its first few ticks and as it goes does more damage per tick until the final 2-3 ticks that do about 200 each.</P><P>Yes I know that in the "misc" section of the spell file there is already a spell called Feast of Blood that is on a rogue weapon. I couldnt come up with anything better at the moment. If anyone know of any horrible afflictions that eat all of your red blood cells or make blood come pouring out your body we can name it that. :)</P><P>So what we would have there is high end necros get spells like Arch Lich and Funeral Pyre where are really good spells and we get the disease based tap. </P><P>Then...</P><P>While I hate this kind of sepretism this is just the way EQ is, its a sepratists game.</P><P>The REALLY uber necros get the 4 Ancient spells to fill out their line with. So they will have:</P><P>Ancient: Master of Death - upgradede Lich (live spell)<BR>Ancient: Lifebane - Unresistable Lifetap (live spell) (very expensive mana/dam cost)<BR>Ancient: River of Blood - Vesing Mordania upgrade (my own concoction)<BR>Ancient: Feast of Blood - Splurt upgrade (my own concoction as well)</P><P>Of course this is just talking spells...</P><P>Pets really need an upgrade. I dont care that pets on raids are worthless because of pathing, and mage epic pets do more. I dont want to be using a 4 exapnsion old weapon. The only thing they need to do for pets is to get rid of the xp penalty on using one, and increase the durability of them. </P><P>I want a pet that can resist some spells and take/block some more hits. I want it to have more life and be of a higher base level so it hits more often and it should not take my xp away from me. No other class in the game loses xp for using the items or spells given to it to take down mobs and gain xp. NONE.</P><P>Philiak Mortus Lv.53 Necromancer of Xev<BR>Zeratis Lv.30 Monkey<BR>Sam: Where should I put this thing so that it doesnt hurt anyone we know or care about?<BR>Max: Out the window Sam. There's nobody but strangers out there.<BR><a href="http://www.pvponline.com" target="_blank">www.pvponline.com</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
