        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> You need to bump wizards to the top.  Most wizards at the end game have a clickable DD robe.  These robes generate a huge amount of damage in fights over 5min (which is pretty much everything).  While you are sitting waiting on your 2k dot to finish a wizard will be chain nuking with the robe and doing roughly 5-7k dmg per min.  Because DOT's DONT stack we cannot even come close to that number.  That is the inherent problem.  Remove clickable DD's for wizards and you come closer to narrowing the gap.   However with DB/high dmg DD + crits the gap is still wide.</P><P>However a necro would outdamage a single wizard without some clickable DD robe.  But in a raid where you have multiple necros its like having one divided.  So if you claim, as a necro, that you can do 50k+ damage at fights like THO etc then you need to divide what your maximum solo damage number/the number of necros on the raid.</P><P><BR>Sindaan Sarcophagus<BR>60, Karana<BR>Grey Hawke<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65075" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65075</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
